On The Bump, WWE revealed the rules for the upcoming WWE Draft. The Draft will begin on the upcoming April 26 episode of WWE SmackDown and continue on the April 29 episode of WWE RAW.

The Rules are as follows:

*   _On SmackDown, there will be_ **_Four Rounds, 16 Total Picks_**
    
*   _On RAW, there will be_ **_Six Rounds, 24 Total Picks_**
    
*   _Champions on each brand are protected_
    
*   _Women’s Tag-Team Champions are eligible to be drafted_
    
*   _SmackDown will pick_ **_first_** _on Friday_
    
*   _RAW will pick_ **_first_** _on Monday_
    
*   _Roster picks will lock-in on_ **_Monday, May 6_**
    

Wrestlers eligible in each respective Draft pools can be seen below (NOTE: NXT talents are also eligible on both nights):

